aS'An integer is called even if it is divisible by 2.'
p9
aS'For integers written in a numeral system based on an even number, such as decimal and hexadecimal, divisibility by 2 is easily tested by merely looking at the last digit.'
p10
aS'If it is even, then the whole number is even.'
p11
aS'In particular, when written in the decimal system, all multiples of 2 will end in 0, 2, 4, 6, or 8.Two is the smallest and the first prime number, and the only even prime number  (for this reason it is sometimes called "the oddest prime").'
p12
aS'The next prime is three.'
p13
aS'Two and three are the only two consecutive prime numbers.'
p14
aS'2 is the first Sophie Germain prime, the first factorial prime, the first Lucas prime, the first Ramanujan prime, and the first Smarandache-Wellin prime.'
p15
aS'(The Ancient Romans usually wrote 4 as IIII, but this was almost entirely replaced by the subtractive notation IV in the Middle Ages.)'
p16
aS'To this day 3 is written as three lines in Roman and Chinese numerals.'
p17
aS'This was the way the Brahmin Indians wrote it, and the Gupta made the three lines more curved.'
p18
aS'The Nagari started rotating the lines clockwise and ending each line with a slight downward stroke on the right.'
p19
aS'Eventually they made these strokes connect with the lines below, and evolved it to a character that looks very much like a modern 3 with an extra stroke at the bottom.'
p20
aS'It was the Western Ghubar Arabs who finally eliminated the extra stroke and created our modern 3.'
p21
aS'(The "extra" stroke, however, was very important to the Eastern Arabs, and they made it much larger, while rotating the strokes above to lie along a horizontal axis, and to this day Eastern Arabs write a 3 that looks like a mirrored 7 with ridges on its top line): 3While the shape of the 3 character has an ascender in most modern typefaces, in typefaces with text figures the character usually has a descender, as, for example, in .'
p22
aS'Four is the only number that has the same number of characters as its value in the English language. In mathematics Four is the smallest composite number, its proper divisors being 1 and 2.'
p23
aS'Four is also a highly composite number.'
p24
aS'The next highly composite number is 6.Four is the second square number, the second centered triangular number.4 is the smallest squared prime (p2) and the only even number in this form.'
p25
aS'It has an aliquot sum of 3 which is itself prime.'
p26
aS'The aliquot sequence of 4 has 4 members (4, 3, 1, 0) and is accordingly the first member of the 3-aliquot tree.A number is a multiple of 4 if its last two digits are a multiple of 4.'
p27
aS'For example, 1092 is a multiple of 4 because 92  4x23.Only one number has an aliquot sum of 4 and that is squared prime 9.The prime factorization of four is two times two.Four is the smallest composite number that is equal to the sum of its prime factors.'
p28
aS'(As a consequence of this, it is the smallest Smith number).'
p29
aS'Because it can be written as 221+1, five is classified as a Fermat prime; therefore a regular polygon with 5 sides (a regular pentagon) is constructible with compass and unmarked straightedge.'
p30
aS'5 is the third Sophie Germain prime, the first safe prime, the third Catalan number, and the third Mersenne prime exponent.'
p31
aS'Five is the first Wilson prime and the third factorial prime, also an alternating factorial.'
p32
aS'Five is the first good prime.'
p33
aS'It is an Eisenstein prime with no imaginary part and real part of the form .'
p34
aS'It is also the only number that is part of more than one pair of twin primes.'
p35
aS'Five is a congruent number.'
