aS'Since 1896, systematic archaeological investigations of the Corinth Excavations by the American School of Classical Studies at Athens have revealed large parts of the ancient city, and recent excavations conducted by the Greek Ministry of Culture have brought important new facets of antiquity to light.For Christians, Corinth is known from the two books First Corinthians and Second Corinthians in the New Testament.'
