p3171
aS'The systematic use in chemistry dates to 1850. Chemical formula Ethanol is a 2-carbon alcohol.'
p3172
aS'It is the simplest alkene (a hydrocarbon with carbon-carbon double bonds), and the second simplest unsaturated hydrocarbon after acetylene (C2H2).Ethylene is widely used in chemical industry, and its worldwide production (over 109 million tonnes in 2006) exceeds that of any other organic compound.'
