aS'One major difference is that fungal cells have cell walls that contain chitin, unlike the cell walls of plants and some protists, which contain cellulose, and unlike the cell walls of bacteria.'
p3628
aS'These and other differences show that the fungi form a single group of related organisms, named the Eumycota (true fungi or Eumycetes), that share a common ancestor (is a monophyletic group).'
p3629
aS'This fungal group is distinct from the structurally similar myxomycetes (slime molds) and oomycetes (water molds).'
p3630
