p6747
aS'They can be quantitatively calculated using the Hartree-Fock or self-consistent field (SCF) methods. Overview A molecular orbital (MO) can be used to represent the regions in a molecule where an electron occupying that orbital is likely to be found.'
p6748
aS'Molecular_orbitals are obtained from the combination of atomic orbitals, which predict the location of an electron in an atom.'
