aS'Phagocytosis is involved in the acquisition of nutrients for some cells.'
p7655
aS"The process is homologous to eating at the level of single-celled organisms; in multicellular animals, the process has been adapted to eliminate debris and pathogens, as opposed to taking in fuel for cellular processes, except in the case of the animal Trichoplax.In an organism's immune system, phagocytosis is a major mechanism used to remove pathogens and cell debris."
p7656
aS'For example, when a macrophage ingests a pathogenic microorganism, the pathogen becomes trapped in a phagosome which then fuses with a lysosome to form a phagolysosome.'
