aS'Pions are the lightest mesons (and, more generally, the lightest hadrons), because they are composed of the lightest quarks (the u and d quarks).'
p7774
aS'They are unstable, with the charged pions p+ and p- decaying with a mean lifetime of 26 nanoseconds (69922600000000000002.6x10-8 seconds), and the neutral pion p0 decaying with a much shorter lifetime of 69838400000000000008.4x10-17 seconds.'
p7775
aS'Charged pions most often decay into muons and muon neutrinos, and neutral pions into gamma rays.The exchange of virtual pions, along with the vector, rho and omega mesons, provides an explanation for the residual strong force between nucleons.'
p7776
