aS'When implemented well, it can be about two or three times faster than its main competitors, merge sort and heapsort.Quicksort is a comparison sort, meaning that it can sort items of any type for which a "less-than" relation (formally, a total order) is defined.'
p8082
aS'In efficient implementations it is not a stable sort, meaning that the relative order of equal sort items is not preserved.'
p8083
aS'Quicksort can operate in-place on an array, requiring small additional amounts of memory to perform the sorting.Mathematical analysis of quicksort shows that, on average, the algorithm takes O(n log n) comparisons to sort n items.'
p8084
aS'In the worst case, it makes O(n2) comparisons, though this behavior is rare. History The quicksort algorithm was developed in 1960 by Tony Hoare while in the Soviet Union, as a visiting student at Moscow State University.'
p8085
