aS'Indeed, an adaptation in a population of one species (e.g.'
p8180
aS'predators, parasites) may change the natural selection pressure on a population of another species (e.g.'
p8181
aS'prey, hosts), giving rise to an antagonistic coevolution.'
p8182
aS'If this positive feedback occurs reciprocally, a potential dynamic coevolution may result.In another idea, the Red_Queen_hypothesis is used independently by Hartung  and Bell to explain the evolution of sex, by John Jaenike to explain the maintenance of sex and W. D. Hamilton to explain the role of sex in response to parasites.'
