aS"Descartes's influence in mathematics is equally apparent; the Cartesian coordinate system -- allowing reference to a point in space as a set of numbers, and allowing algebraic equations to be expressed as geometric shapes in a two- or three-dimensional coordinate system (and conversely, shapes to be described as equations) -- was named after him."
p8215
aS'He is credited as the father of analytical geometry, the bridge between algebra and geometry, crucial to the discovery of infinitesimal calculus and analysis.'
