aS'Whether genetic drift is a minor or major contributor to speciation is the subject matter of much ongoing discussion.There are four geographic modes of speciation in nature, based on the extent to which speciating populations are isolated from one another: allopatric, peripatric, parapatric, and sympatric.'
p8950
aS'Speciation may also be induced artificially, through animal husbandry, agriculture, or laboratory experiments.Charles Darwin was the first to describe the role of natural selection in speciation.'
p8951
aS'There is research into the effects of sexual selection on speciation but no firm conclusions have yet been drawn. Natural speciation All forms of natural speciation have taken place over the course of evolution; however, debate persists as to the relative importance of each mechanism in driving biodiversity.One example of natural speciation is the diversity of the three-spined stickleback, a marine fish that, after the last ice age, has undergone speciation into new freshwater colonies in isolated lakes and streams.'
p8952
aS'Over an estimated 10,000 generations, the sticklebacks show structural differences that are greater than those seen between different genera of fish including variations in fins, changes in the number or size of their bony plates, variable jaw structure, and color differences. Speciation rate There is debate as to the rate at which speciation events occur over geologic time.'
p8953
aS'While some evolutionary biologists claim that speciation events have remained relatively constant over time, some palaeontologists such as Niles Eldredge and Stephen Jay Gould have argued that species usually remain unchanged over long stretches of time, and that speciation occurs only over relatively brief intervals, a view known as punctuated equilibrium.'
