aS'The climate--including wind and rain--creates surface features similar to those of Earth, such as dunes, rivers, lakes, seas (probably of liquid methane-ethane), and deltas, and is dominated by seasonal weather patterns as on Earth.'
p10252
aS"With its liquids (both surface and subsurface) and robust nitrogen atmosphere, Titan's methane cycle is analogous to Earth's water cycle, although at a much lower temperature. History Titan was discovered on March 25, 1655 by the Dutch astronomer Christiaan Huygens."
