aS'The distinguishing structural characteristic of tryptophan is that it contains an indole functional group. Isolation The isolation of tryptophan was first reported by Frederick Hopkins in 1901 through hydrolysis of casein.'
p10437
aS'From 600 grams of crude casein one obtains 4-8 grams of tryptophan. Biosynthesis and industrial production Plants and microorganisms commonly synthesize tryptophan from shikimic acid or anthranilate.'
